# Wine Quality Analysis

## 📌 Overview
This project investigates how chemical properties influence wine quality using statistical analysis and visualization techniques. The goal is to identify key variables that can help predict wine ratings and improve production insights.

---

## 📊 Dataset
- Source: UCI Wine Quality Dataset
- Features:
  - Acidity
  - Residual sugar
  - pH
  - Alcohol content
  - Density

---

## 🛠 Methods

- Data cleaning and preprocessing
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Correlation analysis
- Regression modeling

---

## 📈 Key Findings

- **Alcohol content** showed the strongest positive correlation with wine quality
- **Higher acidity** was associated with lower quality ratings
- Some variables (e.g., residual sugar) had weaker predictive power than expected

